 q = \begin{bmatrix}  cos(\theta/2) \\  \omega_x \sin(\theta/2) \\ \omega_y \sin(\theta/2) \\ \omega_z \sin(\theta/2)\end{bmatrix} = \begin{bmatrix} w \\ x \\ y \\ z\end{bmatrix}
\theta = \operatorname{atan2}(\|\begin{bmatrix}x & y & z\end{bmatrix}\|, w)
 \omega = \frac{\begin{bmatrix} x & y & z\end{bmatrix}^T}{\|\begin{bmatrix}x & y & z\end{bmatrix}\|}
\omega = \operatorname{nullspace}(R - I)
